<!--
  Template: Welcome & Account Activation for Donors
  File: 04-welcome-donation-activation.mjml
  Category: welcome / onboarding
  
  Purpose:
  Welcome new donors after first donation and prompt account activation to access donor portal.
  Combines gratitude, mission reinforcement, and practical account setup in one flow.
  
  When to send:
  - Immediately after first donation is confirmed (within 5-15 minutes)
  - After recurring donation signup
  - After major one-time contribution (threshold-based)
  - NPO/charity/cause-driven organizations only
  
  Personalize:
  - {{firstName}} or {{first_name}}
  - {{activationLink}} - unique account activation URL
  - {{donationAmount}} (optional, can add "Your $50 gift")
  - {{projectName}} (optional, specific project funded)
  - Brand colors (#34c759 primary green, #d5f5e3 light green, #257a3e dark green)
  
  Tested on:
  Gmail (web/mobile), Outlook, Apple Mail, iOS Mail
  
  Notes:
  - Transactional email (account activation = no unsubscribe required in most jurisdictions)
  - Emotional hook: gratitude + impact storytelling ("plant, protect, educate")
  - Hero image: heart made of leaves = visual metaphor for mission
  - Single primary CTA: "Activate My Donor Account" (clear action)
  - Fallback link provided for accessibility
  - Mission reinforcement section = donor retention strategy
  - Works for environmental, humanitarian, animal welfare, education NGOs
  - Activation link should expire (24-48h) for security
  
  Conversion goal:
  Primary: Achieve 60-80% account activation rate
  Secondary: Build emotional connection with cause/mission
  Tertiary: Drive social media follows for ongoing engagement
  
  Design notes:
  - Green palette (#34c759, #d5f5e3, #257a3e) = nature, growth, hope
  - Heart leaf image = emotional + mission-aligned visual
  - Three-tone background sections = visual hierarchy (light â†’ medium â†’ dark â†’ light)
  - Emoji usage (ðŸŒ¿) = friendly, approachable tone
  - 7 social icons = omnichannel community building
  
  Donor psychology:
  - Immediate gratitude = reinforces positive decision
  - Impact framing: "plant, protect, educate" = tangible outcomes
  - Future benefits: "manage donations, download receipts" = practical value
  - Community language: "Together, Let's Grow" = collective mission
  - Transparency offer: "real impact reports" = trust building
  
  A/B test suggestions:
  - Subject line: "Welcome to the family!" vs. "Activate your donor account"
  - CTA copy: "Activate Account" vs. "See My Impact"
  - Add donation confirmation: "Your $X is already at work"
  - Include progress bar: "X trees planted thanks to donors like you"
  
  Best practices:
  - Send immediately after donation (strike while motivation is hot)
  - Keep tone warm, mission-focused (not transactional)
  - Provide fallback link (email clients may block buttons)
  - Emphasize tangible benefits of activation (receipts, reports, updates)
  - Link to social proof (project photos, impact videos)
  
  Security notes:
  - Activation link must be unique, time-limited (24-48h)
  - Use HTTPS for activation URL
  - Consider 2FA option for high-value donor accounts
  - Log activation attempts for fraud detection
-->
